{
  "texts": [
    "The experimental procedure was similar to study 1, but we employed two additional measures of preference.",
    "Thus, in addition to perceived reliability, comprehensibility, and empathy, we also measured the individual willingness to follow the provided advice.",
    "To further test the robustness of our survey instruments, we also slightly adapted the scales on which participants rated the respective dimensions.",
    "That is, we used 5point Likert scales (instead of 7-point as in study 1) going from \"Very unreliable\" to \"Very reliable\", from \"Very difficult to understand\" to \"Very easy to understand\", from \"Very unempathic\" to \"Very empathic\" and from \"Very unwilling\" to \"Very willing\", respectively.",
    "Moreover, at the end of the experiment, participants had the opportunity to save a (fictious) link to the platform and tool, which supposedly generated the previously encountered responses."
  ]
}